-- Microsoft Settles Suit Against Internet Cafe Chain, SCMP Reports
-- B y   D e b r a   M a o
-- 2010-11-24T00:34:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-24/microsoft-settles-suit-against-internet-cafe-chain-scmp-reports.html
Microsoft Corp. reached a settlement
in its copyright infringement lawsuit against Chinese internet
cafe chain Tonecan Network Communications, the South China
Morning Post reported.  The Guangdong province-based Internet cafe operator agreed
to pay an undisclosed amount to the U.S. software maker and
commit to using genuine Microsoft software, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Debra Mao in Hong Kong at 
 dmao5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
